name: Croagunk
pokedex_description: Its cheeks hold poison sacs. It tries to catch foes off guard to jab them with toxic fingers.

name: Toxicroak
pokedex_description: Its knuckle claws secrete a toxin so vile that even a scratch could prove fatal.

name: Carnivine
pokedex_description: It attracts prey with its sweet-smelling saliva, then chomps down. It takes a whole day to eat prey.

name: Finneon
pokedex_description: After long exposure to sunlight, the patterns on its tail fins shine vividly when darkness arrives.

name: Lumineon
pokedex_description: It lives on the deep-sea floor. It attracts prey by flashing the patterns on its four tail fins.

name: Mantyke
pokedex_description: A friendly Pokémon that captures the subtle flows of seawater using its two antennae.

name: Snover
pokedex_description: It lives on snowy mountains. Having had little contact with humans, it is boldly inquisitive.

name: Abomasnow
pokedex_description: It whips up blizzards in mountains that are always buried in snow. It is the abominable snowman.

name: Weavile
pokedex_description: They live in cold regions, forming groups of four or five that hunt prey with impressive coordination.

name: Magnezone
pokedex_description: It evolved from exposure to a special magnetic field. Three units generate magnetism.

name: Lickilicky
pokedex_description: It wraps things with its extensible tongue. Getting too close to it will leave you soaked with drool.

name: Rhyperior
pokedex_description: It puts rocks in holes in its palms and uses its muscles to shoot them. Geodude are shot at rare times.

name: Tangrowth
pokedex_description: Las enredaderas han crecido, protegiendo aún mejor su cuerpo y aportándole nuevas estructuras como grandes brazos extensibles.

name: Electivire
pokedex_description: It pushes the tips of its two tails against the foe, then lets loose with over 20,000 volts of power.

name: Magmortar
pokedex_description: It blasts fireballs of over 3,600 degrees F from the ends of its arms. It lives in volcanic craters.

name: Togekiss
pokedex_description: It will never appear where there is strife. Its sightings have become rare recently.

name: Yanmega
pokedex_description: By churning its wings, it creates shock waves that inflict critical internal injuries to foes.

name: Leafeon
pokedex_description: Es de las mutaciones más drásticas de Eevee ya que desarrolla estructuras que le permiten realizar la fotosíntesis o fecundar con su polen a distancia.

name: Glaceon
pokedex_description: Está muy bien adaptado al frio ya que su sangre tiene una sustancia anticongelante que evita que su cuerpo se congele incluso a -200ºC.

name: Gliscor
pokedex_description: It observes prey while hanging inverted from branches. When the chance presents itself, it swoops!

name: Mamoswine
pokedex_description: Its impressive tusks are made of ice. The population thinned when it turned warm after the ice age.

name: Porygon-Z
pokedex_description: Additional software was installed to make it a better Pokémon. It began acting oddly, however.

name: Gallade
pokedex_description: A master of courtesy and swordsmanship, it fights using extending swords on its elbows.

name: Probopass
pokedex_description: It exudes strong magnetism from all over. It controls three small units called Mini-Noses.

name: Dusknoir
pokedex_description: The antenna on its head captures radio waves from the world of spirits that command it to take people there.

name: Froslass
pokedex_description: Se dice que es el alma de una bella mujer fallecida en la nieve. Aparece en tormentas nevadas y congela a viajeros atrapados en ellas.

name: Rotom
pokedex_description: Its body is composed of plasma. It is known to infiltrate electronic devices and wreak havoc.

name: Uxie
pokedex_description: Known as “The Being of Knowledge.” It is said that it can wipe out the memory of those who see its eyes.

name: Mesprit
pokedex_description: Known as “The Being of Emotion.” It taught humans the nobility of sorrow, pain, and joy.

name: Azelf
pokedex_description: Known as “The Being of Willpower.” It sleeps at the bottom of a lake to keep the world in balance.

name: Dialga
pokedex_description: It has the power to control time. It appears in Sinnoh-region myths as an ancient deity.

name: Palkia
pokedex_description: It has the ability to distort space. It is described as a deity in Sinnoh-region mythology.

name: Heatran
pokedex_description: It dwells in volcanic caves. It digs in with its cross-shaped feet to crawl on ceilings and walls.

name: Regigigas
pokedex_description: There is an enduring legend that states this Pokémon towed continents with ropes.

name: Giratina
pokedex_description: A Pokémon that is said to live in a world on the reverse side of ours. It appears in an ancient cemetery.

name: Cresselia
pokedex_description: Shiny particles are released from its wings like a veil. It is said to represent the crescent moon.

name: Phione
pokedex_description: A Pokémon that lives in warm seas. It inflates the flotation sac on its head to drift and search for food.

name: Manaphy
pokedex_description: Born on a cold seafloor, it will swim great distances to return to its birthplace.

name: Darkrai
pokedex_description: It can lull people to sleep and make them dream. It is active during nights of the new moon.

name: Shaymin
pokedex_description: It lives in flower patches and avoids detection by curling up to look like a flowering plant.

name: Arceus
pokedex_description: It is described in mythology as the Pokémon that shaped the universe with its 1,000 arms.

name: Victini
pokedex_description: This Pokémon brings victory. It is said that Trainers with Victini always win, regardless of the type of encounter.

name: Snivy
pokedex_description: They photosynthesize by bathing their tails in sunlight. When they are not feeling well, their tails droop.

name: Servine
pokedex_description: They avoid attacks by sinking into the shadows of thick foliage. They retaliate with masterful whipping techniques.

name: Serperior
pokedex_description: They raise their heads to intimidate opponents, but only give it their all when fighting a powerful opponent.

name: Tepig
pokedex_description: It blows fire through its nose. When it catches a cold, the fire becomes pitch-black smoke instead.

name: Pignite
pokedex_description: Whatever it eats becomes fuel for the flame in its stomach. When it is angered, the intensity of the flame increases.

name: Emboar
pokedex_description: It can throw a fire punch by setting its fists on fire with its fiery chin. It cares deeply about its friends.

name: Oshawott
pokedex_description: The scalchop on its stomach is made from the same elements as claws. It detaches the scalchop for use as a blade.

name: Dewott
pokedex_description: Scalchop techniques differ from one Dewott to another. It never neglects maintaining its scalchops.

name: Samurott
pokedex_description: Part of the armor on its anterior legs becomes a giant sword. Its cry alone is enough to intimidate most enemies.

name: Patrat
pokedex_description: Extremely cautious, they take shifts to maintain a constant watch of their nest. They feel insecure without a lookout.

name: Watchog
pokedex_description: They make the patterns on their bodies shine in order to threaten predators. Keen eyesight lets them see in the dark.

name: Lillipup
pokedex_description: Es activo, sobreprotector, tranquilo y le encanta que su entrenador le preste atención. Necesitan ejercicio físico diario para estar sanos.

name: Herdier
pokedex_description: No es fácil de adiestrar pero es un buen vigilante, ladra al mínimo movimiento sospechoso o cuando alguien se acerca y parece peligroso.

name: Stoutland
pokedex_description: Es tranquilo, dócil y muy leal. Cuidan de sus seres queridos, su entrenador no dudará en dejarlo al cuidado de sus hijos si debe ausentarse.

name: Purrloin
pokedex_description: Its cute act is a ruse. When victims let down their guard, they find their items taken. It attacks with sharp claws.

name: Liepard
pokedex_description: Stealthily, it sneaks up on its target, striking from behind before its victim has a chance to react.

name: Pansage
pokedex_description: It shares the leaf on its head with weary-looking Pokémon. These leaves are known to relieve stress.

name: Simisage
pokedex_description: Ill tempered, it fights by swinging its barbed tail around wildly. The leaf growing on its head is very bitter.

name: Pansear
pokedex_description: This Pokémon lives in caves in volcanoes. The fire within the tuft on its head can reach 600º F.

name: Simisear
pokedex_description: A flame burns inside its body. It scatters embers from its head and tail to sear its opponents.

name: Panpour
pokedex_description: It does not thrive in dry environments. It keeps itself damp by shooting water stored in its head tuft from its tail.

name: Simipour
pokedex_description: The high-pressure water expelled from its tail is so powerful, it can destroy a concrete wall.

name: Munna
pokedex_description: It eats the dreams of people and Pokémon. When it eats a pleasant dreams, it expels pink-colored mist.

name: Musharna
pokedex_description: With the mist from its forehead, it can create shapes of things from dreams it has eaten.

name: Pidove
pokedex_description: These Pokémon live in cities. They are accustomed to people. Flocks often gather in parks and plazas.

name: Tranquill
pokedex_description: Many people believe that, deep in the forest where Tranquill live, there is a peaceful place where there is no war.

name: Unfezant
pokedex_description: Males have plumage on their heads. They will never let themselves feel close to anyone other than their Trainers.

name: Blitzle
pokedex_description: When thunderclouds cover the sky, it will appear. It can catch lightning with its mane and store the electricity.

name: Zebstrika
pokedex_description: This ill-tempered Pokémon is dangerous because when it's angry, it shoots lightning from its mane in all directions.

name: Roggenrola
pokedex_description: They were discovered a hundred years ago in an earthquake fissure. Inside each one is an energy core.

name: Boldore
pokedex_description: Because its energy was too great to be contained, the energy leaked and formed orange crystals.

name: Gigalith
pokedex_description: The solar energy absorbed by its body's orange crystals is magnified internally and fired from its mouth.

name: Woobat
pokedex_description: Suction from its nostrils enables it to stick to cave walls during sleep. It leaves a heart-shaped mark behind.

name: Swoobat
pokedex_description: Anyone who comes into contact with the ultrasonic waves emitted by a courting male experiences a positive mood shift.

name: Drilbur
pokedex_description: It makes its way swiftly through the soil by putting both claws together and rotating at high speed.

name: Excadrill
pokedex_description: More than 300 feet below the surface, they build mazelike nests. Their activity can be destructive to subway tunnels.

name: Audino
pokedex_description: Its auditory sense is astounding. It has a radar-like ability to understand its surrounding through slight sounds.

name: Timburr
pokedex_description: These Pokémon appear at building sites and help out with construction. They always carry squared logs.

name: Gurdurr
pokedex_description: They strengthen their bodies by carrying steel beams. They show off their big muscles to their friends.

name: Conkeldurr
pokedex_description: They use concrete pillars as walking canes. They know moves that enable them to swing the pillars freely in battle.

name: Tympole
pokedex_description: By vibrating its cheeks, it emits sound waves imperceptible to humans. It uses the rhythm of these sounds to talk.

name: Palpitoad
pokedex_description: It lives in the water and on land. It uses its long, sticky tongue to capture prey.

name: Seismitoad
pokedex_description: It increases the power of its punches by vibrating the bumps on its fists. It can turn a boulder to rubble with one punch.

name: Throh
pokedex_description: When they encounter foes bigger than themselves, they try to throw them. They always travel in packs of five.

name: Sawk
pokedex_description: Tying their belts gets them pumped and makes their punches more destructive. Disturbing their training angers them.

name: Sewaddle
pokedex_description: This Pokémon makes clothes for itself. It chews up leaves and sews them with sticky thread extruded from its mouth.

name: Swadloon
pokedex_description: It protects itself from the cold by wrapping up in leaves. It stays on the move, eating leaves in forests.

name: Leavanny
pokedex_description: It keeps its eggs warm with heat from fermenting leaves. It also uses leaves to make warm wrappings for Sewaddle.

name: Venipede
pokedex_description: It discovers what is going on around it by using the feelers on its head and tail. It is brutally aggresive.

name: Whirlipede
pokedex_description: It is usually motionless, but when attacked, it rotates at high speed and then crashes into its opponent.

name: Scolipede
pokedex_description: Highly aggressive, it uses the claws near its neck to dig into its opponents and poison them.

name: Cottonee
pokedex_description: They go wherever the wind takes them. On rainy days, their bodies are heavier, so they take shelter beneath big trees.

name: Whimsicott
pokedex_description: Riding whirlwinds, they appear. These Pokémon sneak through gaps into houses and cause all sorts of mischief.

name: Petilil
pokedex_description: Since they prefer moist, nutrient-rich soil, the areas where Petilil live are known to be good for growing plants.

name: Lilligant
pokedex_description: The fragrance of the garland on its head has a relaxing effect. It withers if a Trainer does not take good care of it.

name: Basculin
pokedex_description: Red and blue Basculin usually do not get along, but sometimes members of one school mingle with the other's schooL.

name: Sandile
pokedex_description: It moves along below the sand's surface, except for its nose and eyes. A dark membrane shields its eyes from the sun.

name: Krokorok
pokedex_description: The special membrane covering its eyes can sense the heat of objects, so it can see its surroundings, even in darkness.

name: Krookodile
pokedex_description: It can expand the focus of its eyes, enabling it to see objects in the far distance as if it were using binoculars.

name: Darumaka
pokedex_description: Darumaka's droppings are hot, so people used to put them in their clothes to keep themselves warm.

name: Darmanitan
pokedex_description: When weakened in battle, it transforms into a stone statue. Then it sharpens its mind and fights on mentally.

name: Maractus
pokedex_description: Arid regions are their habitat. They move rhythmically, making a sound similar to maracas.

name: Dwebble
pokedex_description: It makes a hole in a suitable rock. If that rock breaks, the Pokémon remains agitated until it locates a replacement.

name: Crustle
pokedex_description: It possesses legs of enormous strength, enabling it to carry heavy slabs for many days, even when crossing arid land.

name: Scraggy
pokedex_description: It immediately headbutts anyone that makes eye contact with it. Its skull is massively thick.

name: Scrafty
pokedex_description: It can smash concrete blocks with its kicking attacks. The one with the biggest crest is the group leader.

name: Sigilyph
pokedex_description: The guardians of an ancient city, they use their psychic power to attack enemies that invade their territory.

name: Yamask
pokedex_description: These Pokémon arose from the spirits of people interred in graves in past ages. Each retains memories of its former life.

name: Cofagrigus
pokedex_description: They pretend to be elaborate coffins to teach lessons to grave robbers. Their bodies are covered in pure gold.

name: Tirtouga
pokedex_description: About 100 million years ago, these Pokémon swam in oceans. It is thought they also went on land to attack prey.

name: Carracosta
pokedex_description: Incredible jaw strength enables them to chew up steel beams and rocks along with their prey.

name: Archen
pokedex_description: Revived from a fossil, this Pokémon is thought to be the ancestor of all bird Pokémon.

name: Archeops
pokedex_description: It runs better than it flies. It catches prey by running at speeds comparable to those of an automobile.

name: Trubbish
pokedex_description: The combination of garbage bags and industrial waste caused the chemical reaction that crated this Pokémon.

name: Garbodor
pokedex_description: They absorb garbage and make it part of their bodies. They shoot a poisonous liquid from their right-hand fingertips.

name: Zorua
pokedex_description: To protect themselves from danger, they hide their true identities by transforming into people and Pokémon.

name: Zoroark
pokedex_description: Each has the ability to fool a large group of people simultaneously. They protect their lair with illusory scenery.

name: Minccino
pokedex_description: These Pokémon prefer a tidy habitat. They are always sweeping and dusting, using their tails as brooms.

name: Cinccino
pokedex_description: Their white fur feels amazing to touch. Their fur repels dust and prevents static electricity from building up.

name: Gothita
pokedex_description: They intently observe both Trainers and Pokémon. Apparently, they are looking at something that only Gothita can see.

name: Gothorita
pokedex_description: Starlight is the source of their power. At night, they mark star positions by using psychic power to float stones.

name: Gothitelle
pokedex_description: They can predict the future from the placement and movement of the stars. They can see Trainers' life spans.

name: Solosis
pokedex_description: Because their bodies are enveloped in a special liquid, they can survive in any environment.

name: Duosion
pokedex_description: When their brains, now divided in two, are thinking the same thoughts, these Pokémon exhibit their maximum power.

name: Reuniclus
pokedex_description: These remarkably intelligent Pokémon fight by controlling arms that can grip with rock-crushing power.

name: Ducklett
pokedex_description: When attacked, it uses its feathers to splash water, escaping under cover of the spray.

name: Swanna
pokedex_description: It administers sharp, powerful pecks with its bill. It whips its long neck to deliver forceful repeated strikes.

name: Vanillite
pokedex_description: This Pokémon formed from icicles bathed in energy from the morning sun. It sleeps buried in snow.

name: Vanillish
pokedex_description: It conceals itself from enemy eyes by creating many small ice particles and hiding among them.

name: Vanilluxe
pokedex_description: If both heads get angry simultaneously, this Pokémon expels a blizzard, burying everything in snow.

name: Deerling
pokedex_description: The turning of the seasons changes the color and scent of this Pokémon's fur. People use it to mark the seasons.

name: Sawsbuck
pokedex_description: The plants growing on its horns change according to the season. The leaders of the herd possess magnificent horns.

name: Emolga
pokedex_description: They live on treetops and glide using the inside of a cape-like membrane while discharging electricity.

name: Karrablast
pokedex_description: When they feel threatened, they spit an acidic liquid to drive attackers away. This Pokémon targets Shelmet.

name: Escavalier
pokedex_description: These Pokémon evolve by wearing the shell covering of a Shelmet. The steel armor protects their whole body.

name: Foongus
pokedex_description: For some reason, this Pokémon resembles a Poké Ball. They release poison spores to repel those who try to catch them.

name: Amoonguss
pokedex_description: They show off their Poké Ball caps to lure prey, but very few Pokémon are fooled by this.

name: Frillish
pokedex_description: They paralyze prey with poison, then drag them down to their lairs, five miles below the surface.

name: Jellicent
pokedex_description: They propel themselves by expelling absorbed seawater from their bodies. Their favorite food is life energy.

name: Alomomola
pokedex_description: Floating in the open sea is how they live. When they find a wounded Pokémon, they embrace it and bring it to shore.

name: Joltik
pokedex_description: They attach themselves to large-bodied Pokémon and absorb static electricity, which they store in an electric pouch.

name: Galvantula
pokedex_description: They employ an electrically charged web to trap their prey. While it is immobilized by shock, they leisurely consume it.

name: Ferroseed
pokedex_description: They stick their spikes into cave walls and absorb the minerals they find in the rock.

name: Ferrothorn
pokedex_description: They attach themselves to cave ceilings, firing steel spikes at targets passing beneath them.

name: Klink
pokedex_description: Interlocking two bodies and spinning around generates the energy they need to live.

name: Klang
pokedex_description: Spinning minigears are rotated at high speed and repeatedly fired away. It is dangerous if the gears don't return.

name: Klinklang
pokedex_description: The gear with the red core is rotated at high speed for a rapid energy charge.

name: Tynamo
pokedex_description: These Pokémon move in schools. They have an electricity-generating organ, so they discharge electricity if in danger.

name: Eelektrik
pokedex_description: These Pokémon have a big appetite. When they spot their prey, they attack it and paralyze it with electricity.

name: Eelektross
pokedex_description: With their sucker mouths, they suck in prey. Then they use their fangs to shock the prey with electricity.

name: Elgyem
pokedex_description: This Pokémon had never been seen until it appeared from far in the desert 50 years ago.

name: Beheeyem
pokedex_description: It uses psychic power to control an opponent's brain and tamper with its memories.

name: Litwick
pokedex_description: While shining a light and pretending to be a guide, it leeches off the life force of any who follow it.

name: Lampent
pokedex_description: It arrives near the moment of death and steals spirit from the body.

name: Chandelure
pokedex_description: Being consumed in Chandelure's flame burns up the spirit, leaving the body behind.

name: Axew
pokedex_description: They mark their territory by leaving gashes in trees with their tusks. If a tusk breaks, a new one grows in quickly.

name: Fraxure
pokedex_description: Their tusks can shatter rocks. Territory battles between Fraxure can be intensely violent.

name: Haxorus
pokedex_description: Their sturdy tusks will stay sharp even if used to cut steel beams. These Pokémon are covered in hard armor.

name: Cubchoo
pokedex_description: Its nose is always running. It sniffs the snot back up because the mucus provides the raw material for its moves.

name: Beartic
pokedex_description: It freezes its breath to create fangs and claws of ice to fight with. Cold northern areas are its habitat.

name: Cryogonal
pokedex_description: They are born in snow clouds. They use chains made of ice crystals to capture prey.

name: Shelmet
pokedex_description: It evolves when bathed in an electric-like energy along with Karrablast. The reason is still unknown.

name: Accelgor
pokedex_description: Having removed its heavy shell, it becomes very light and can fight with ninja-like movements.

name: Stunfisk
pokedex_description: It conceals itself in the mud of the seashore. Then it waits. When prey touch it, it delivers a jolt of energy.

name: Mienfoo
pokedex_description: They have mastered elegant combos. As they concentrate, their battle moves become swifter and more precise.

name: Mienshao
pokedex_description: They use the long fur on their arms as a whip to strike their opponents.

name: Druddigon
pokedex_description: It races through narrow caves, using its sharp claws to catch prey. Then skin on its face is harder than a rock.

name: Golett
pokedex_description: These Pokémon are thought to have been created by the science of an ancient and mysterious civilization.

name: Golurk
pokedex_description: It is said that Golurk were ordered to protect people and Pokémon by the ancient people who made them.

name: Pawniard
pokedex_description: Descendiente de una larga estirpe de Bisharp que lucharon en los tercios españoles, entrena duro para llegar a ser tan diestro como sus antecesores.

name: Bisharp
pokedex_description: Algunos fueron contratados como mercenarios por los tercios españoles y con el tiempo adoptaron las ropas y técnicas de combate de estos soldados.

name: Bouffalant
pokedex_description: They charge wildly and headbutt everything. They headbutts have enough destructive force to derail a train.

name: Rufflet
pokedex_description: They will challenge anything, even strong opponents, without fear. Their frequent fights help them become stronger.

name: Braviary
pokedex_description: The more scars they have, the more respect these brave soldiers of the sky get from their peers.

name: Vullaby
pokedex_description: They tend to guard their posteriors with suitable bones they have found. They pursue weak Pokémon.

name: Mandibuzz
pokedex_description: Watching from the sky, they swoop to strike weakened Pokémon on the ground. They decorate themselves with bones.

name: Heatmor
pokedex_description: Using their very hot, flame-covered tongues, they burn through Durant's steel bodies and consume their insides.

name: Durant
pokedex_description: Durant dig nests in mountains. They build their complicated, interconnected tunnels in mazes.

name: Deino
pokedex_description: They cannot see, so they tackle and bite to learn about their surroundings. Their bodies are covered in wounds.

name: Zweilous
pokedex_description: Since their two heads do not get along and compete with each other for food, they always eat too much.

name: Hydreigon
pokedex_description: The heads on their arms do not have brains. They use all three heads to consume and destroy everything.

name: Larvesta
pokedex_description: The base of volcanoes is where they make their homes. They shoot fire from their five horns to repel attacking enemies.

name: Volcarona
pokedex_description: A sea of fire engulfs the surroundings of their battles, since they use their six wings to scatter their ember scales.

name: Cobalion
pokedex_description: It has a body and heart of steel. Its glare is sufficient to make even an unruly Pokémon obey it.

name: Terrakion
pokedex_description: Its charge is strong enough to break through a giant castle wall in one blow. This Pokémon is spoken of in legends.

name: Virizion
pokedex_description: Its head sprouts horns as sharp as blades. Using whirlwind-like movements, it confounds and swiftly cuts opponents.

name: Tornadus
pokedex_description: Tornadus expels massive energy from its tail, causing severe storms. Its power is great enough to blow houses away.

name: Thundurus
pokedex_description: The spikes on its tail discharge immense bolts of lightning. It flies around the Unova region firing off lightning bolts.

name: Reshiram
pokedex_description: When Reshiram's tail flares, the heat energy moves the atmosphere and changes the world's weather.

name: Zekrom
pokedex_description: This Pokémon appears in legends. In its tail, it has a giant generator that creates electricity.

name: Landorus
pokedex_description: The energy that comes pouring from its tail increases the nutrition in the soil, making crops grow to great size.

name: Kyurem
pokedex_description: It generates a powerful, freezing energy inside itself, but its body became frozen when the energy leaked out.

name: Keldeo
pokedex_description: It crosses the world, running over the surfaces of oceans and rivers. It appears at scenic waterfronts.

name: Meloetta
pokedex_description: Many famous songs have been inspired by the melodies that Meloetta plays.

name: Genesect
pokedex_description: This ancient bug Pokémon was altered by Team Plasma. They upgraded the cannon on its back.

name: Chespin
pokedex_description: The quills on its head are usually soft. When it flexes them, the points become so hard and sharp that they can pierce rock.

name: Quilladin
pokedex_description: They strengthen their lower bodies by running into one another. They are very kind and won't start fights.

name: Chesnaught
pokedex_description: En el pasado, este Pokémon era un letal cazador de dragones y de otras criaturas voladoras gracias a sus púas.

name: Fennekin
pokedex_description: As it walks, it munches on a twig in place of a snack. It intimidates opponents by puffing hot air out of its ears.

name: Braixen
pokedex_description: When the twig is plucked from its tail, friction sets the twig alight. The flame is used to send signals to its allies.

name: Delphox
pokedex_description: En el pasado, era considerado el mejor de los espadachines. Luchaba bendecido por la tormenta.

name: Froakie
pokedex_description: It protects its skin by covering its body in delicate bubbles. Beneath its happy-go-lucky air, it keeps a watchful eye on its surroundings.

name: Frogadier
pokedex_description: It can throw bubble-covered pebbles with precise control, hitting empty cans up to a hundred feet away.

name: Greninja
pokedex_description: En el pasado, era un maestro del engaño y las ilusiones. Muchos reinos fueron víctima de sus trucos.

name: Bunnelby
pokedex_description: It has ears like shovels. Digging holes strengthens its ears so much that they can sever thick roots effortlessly.

name: Diggersby
pokedex_description: As powerful as an excavator, its ears can reduce dense bedrock to rubble. When it’s finished digging, it lounges lazily.

name: Fletchling
pokedex_description: These friendly Pokemon send signals to one another with beautiful chirps and tail-feather movements.

name: Fletchinder
pokedex_description: The hotter the flame sac on its belly, the faster it can fly, but it takes some time to get the fire going.

name: Talonflame
pokedex_description: In the fever of an exciting battle, it showers embers from the gaps between its feathers and takes to the air.

name: Scatterbug
pokedex_description: The powder that covers its body regulates its temperature, so it can live in any region or climate.

name: Spewpa
pokedex_description: It lives hidden within thicket shadows. When predators attack, it quickly bristles the fur covering its body in an effort to threaten them.

name: Vivillon
pokedex_description: Vivillon with many different patterns are found all over the world. These patterns are affected by the climate of their habitat.

name: Litleo
pokedex_description: They set off on their own from their pride and live by themselves to become stronger. These hot-blooded Pokémon are quick to fight.

name: Pyroar
pokedex_description: With fiery breath of more than 10,000 degrees Fahrenheit, they viciously threaten any challenger. The females protect the pride’s cubs.

name: Flabebe
pokedex_description: When it finds a flower it likes, it dwells on that flower its whole life long. It floats in the wind’s embrace with an untroubled heart.

name: Floette
pokedex_description: It flutters around fields of flowers and cares for flowers that are starting to wilt. It draws out the power of flowers to battle.

name: Florges
pokedex_description: It claims exquisite flower gardens as its territory, and it obtains power from basking in the energy emitted by flowering plants.

name: Skiddo
pokedex_description: Thought to be one of the first Pokemon to live in harmony with humans, it has a placid disposition.

name: Gogoat
pokedex_description: They inhabit mountainous regions. The leader of the herd is decided by a battle of clashing horns.

name: Pancham
pokedex_description: It does its best to be taken seriously by its enemies, but its glare is not sufficiently intimidating. Chewing on a leaf is its trademark.

name: Pangoro
pokedex_description: It charges ahead and bashes its opponents like a berserker, uncaring about any hits it might take. Its arms are mighty enough to snap a telephone pole.

name: Furfrou
pokedex_description: Historically, in the Kalos region, these Pokemon were the designated guardians of the king.

name: Espurr
pokedex_description: It has enough psychic energy to blast everything within 300 feet of itself, but it has no control over its power.

name: Meowstic
pokedex_description: When in danger, it raises its ears and releases enough psychic power to grind a 10-ton truck to dust.

name: Honedge
pokedex_description: Apparently this Pokemon is born when a departed spirit inhabits a sword. It attaches itself to people and drinks their life force.

name: Doublade
pokedex_description: The complex attack patterns of its two swords are unstoppable, even for an opponent greatly accomplished at swordplay.

name: Aegislash
pokedex_description: Apparently, it can detect the innate qualities of leadership. According to legend, whoever it recognizes is destined to become king.

name: Spritzee
pokedex_description: In the past, rather than using perfume, royal ladies carried a Spritzee that would waft a fragrance they liked.

name: Aromatisse
pokedex_description: Its scent is so overpowering that, unless a Trainer happens to really enjoy the smell, he or she will have a hard time walking alongside it.

name: Swirlix
pokedex_description: To entangle its opponents in battle, it extrudes white threads as sweet and as sticky as cotton candy.

name: Slurpuff
pokedex_description: Its sense of smell is 100 million times better than a human’s, so even the faintest scent tells it about everything in the area. It’s like it can see with its nose!

name: Inkay
pokedex_description: It flashes the light-emitting spots on its body, which drains its opponent’s will to fight. It takes the opportunity to scuttle away and hide.

name: Malamar
pokedex_description: It lures its prey close with hypnotic motions, then wraps its tentacles around it before finishing it off with digestive fluids.

name: Binacle
pokedex_description: Two Binacle live together on one rock. When they fight, one of them will move to a different rock.

name: Barbaracle
pokedex_description: Barbaracle's legs and hands have minds of their own, and they will move independently. But they usually follow the head's orders.

name: Skrelp
pokedex_description: Camouflaged as rotten kelp, they spray liquid poison on prey that approaches unawares and then finish it off.

name: Dragalge
pokedex_description: Tales are told of ships that wander into seas where Dragalge live, never to return.

name: Clauncher
pokedex_description: They knock down flying prey by firing compressed water from their massive claws like shooting a pistol.

name: Clawitzer
pokedex_description: Their enormous claws launch cannonballs of water powerful enough to pierce tanker hulls.

name: Helioptile
pokedex_description: They make their home in desserts. They can generate their energy from basking in the sun, so eating food is not a requirement.

name: Heliolisk
pokedex_description: They flare their frills and generate energy. A single Heliolisk can generate sufficiant electricity to power a skyscraper.

name: Tyrunt
pokedex_description: Its immense jaws have enough destructive force that it can chew up an automobile It lived 100 million years ago.

name: Tyrantrum
pokedex_description: Nothing could stop this Pokemon 100 years ago, so it behaved like a king.

name: Amaura
pokedex_description: This ancient Pokemon was restored from part of its body that had been frozen in ice for over 100 million years.

name: Aurorus
pokedex_description: The diamond-shaped crystals on its body expel air as cold as -240 degrees Fahrenheit, surrounding its enemies and encasing them in ice.

name: Sylveon
pokedex_description: Es muy amistoso, cariñoso y alegre. Se preocupa por el bienestar de su entrenador sin poder evitarlo ya que presenta genes que lo incitan a ello.

name: Hawlucha
pokedex_description: Although its body is small, its proficient fighting skills enable it to keep up with big bruisers like Machamp and Hariyama.

name: Dedenne
pokedex_description: It uses its tail to absorb electricity from power plants or from outlets in houses, and then it fires the electricity from its whiskers.

name: Carbink
pokedex_description: It has slept underground for hundreds of millions of years since its birth. It's occasionally found during the excavation of caves.

name: Goomy
pokedex_description: The weakest Dragon-type Pokémon, it lives in damp, shady places, so its body doesn't dry out.

name: Sliggoo
pokedex_description: It drives away opponents by excreting a sticky liquid that can dissolve anything. Its eyes devolved, so it can't see anything.

name: Goodra
pokedex_description: This very friendly Dragon-type Pokemon will hug its beloved Trainer, leaving that Trainer covered in sticky slime.

name: Klefki
pokedex_description: It never lets go of a key that it likes, so people give it the keys to vaults and safes as a way to prevent crime.

name: Phantump
pokedex_description: According to old tales, these Pokémon are stumps possessed by the spirits of children who died while lost in the forest.

name: Trevenant
pokedex_description: It can control trees at will. It will trap people who harm the forest, so they can never leave.

name: Pumpkaboo
pokedex_description: The pumpkin body is inhabited by a spirit trapped in this world. As the sun sets, it becomes restless and active.

name: Gourgeist
pokedex_description: It enwraps its prey in its hairlike arms. It sings joyfully as it observes the suffering of its prey.

name: Bergmite
pokedex_description: It blocks opponents' attacks with the ice that shields its body. It uses cold air to repair any cracks with new ice.

name: Avalugg
pokedex_description: Its ice-covered body is as hard as steel. Its cumbersome frame crushes anything that stands in its way.

name: Noibat
pokedex_description: They live in pitch black caves. Their enormous ears can emit ultrasonic waves of 200,000 hertz.

name: Noivern
pokedex_description: The ultrasonic waves it emits from its ears can reduce a large boulder to pebbles. It swoops out of the dark to attack.

name: Xerneas
pokedex_description: Legends say it can share eternal life. It slept for a thousand years in the form of a tree before its revival.

name: Yveltal
pokedex_description: When its life comes to an end, it absorbs the life energy of every living thing and turns into a cocoon once more.

name: Zygarde
pokedex_description: It's hypothesized that it's monitoring those who destroy the ecosystem from deep in the cave where it lives.

name: Diancie
pokedex_description: A sudden transformation of Carbink, its pink, glimmering body is said to be the loveliest sight in the whole world.

name: Hoopa
pokedex_description: It gathers things it likes and pushes them through its loop to teleport them to a secret place.

name: Volcanion
pokedex_description: It expels its internal steam from the arms on its back. It has enough power to blow away a mountain.

name: Rowlet
pokedex_description: This wary Pokémon uses photosynthesis to store up energy during the day, while becoming active at night.

name: Dartrix
pokedex_description: It spends its free time preening its wings. Its preoccupation with any dirt on its plumage can leave it unable to battle.

name: Decidueye
pokedex_description: It fires arrow quills from its wings with such precision, they can pierce a pebble from over hundred yards.

name: Litten
pokedex_description: While grooming itself, it build up fur inside its stomach. It sets the fur alight and spews fiery attacks, which change based on how it coughs.

name: Torracat
pokedex_description: At its throat, it bears a bell of fire. The bell rings brightly whenever this Pokémon spits fire.

name: Incineroar
pokedex_description: This Pokémon has a violent, selfish disposition. When in a bad mood, it may ignore its Trainer's orders with complete nonchalance.

name: Popplio
pokedex_description: This Pokémon snorts body fluid from its nose, blowing balloons to smash into its foes. It's famous for being a hard worker.

name: Brionne
pokedex_description: A skillful dancer, it creates a sequence of water balloons as it dances, and briskly bombards its enemies.

name: Primarina
pokedex_description: It controls its water balloons by singing. The melody is learned from others of its kind and is passed down a generation.

name: Pikipek
pokedex_description: It can peck at a rate of 16 times a second to drill holes in trees. It uses the holes for food storage and nesting.

name: Trumbeak
pokedex_description: It eats berries and stores their seeds in its beak. When it encounters enemies or Prey, it fires off all the seeds in a burst.

name: Toucannon
pokedex_description: When it battles its beak heats up. The heat can easily exceed 100 degrees Celcius, causing severe burns when it hits.

name: Yungoos
pokedex_description: It wanders around in a never-ending search for food. At dusk, it collapses from exhaustioni and falls asleep on the spot.

name: Gumshoos
pokedex_description: When it finds a trace of its prey, it patiently stakes out the location, but it's always snoozing by nightfall.

name: Grubbin
pokedex_description: Vive en campos o bosques junto a centrales eléctricas. Usa sus potentes mandíbulas para penetrar la corteza de árboles y absorber la savia.

name: Charjabug
pokedex_description: Se mueve muy poco y almacena energía hasta que evoluciona, la cual puede transferirla a objetos u otros Pokémon como si fuera una batería.

name: Vikavolt
pokedex_description: Los machos combaten con sus mandíbulas para disputarse a las hembras. Éstas tras el apareamiento ponen sus huevos en huecos en la corteza de árboles.

name: Crabrawler
pokedex_description: It punches so much, its pincers often come off from overuse, but they grow back quickly.

name: Crabominable
pokedex_description: It aimed for the top but got lost and ended up on a snowy mountain. Being forced to endure the cold, this Pokémon evolved.

name: Oricorio
pokedex_description: It beats its wings together to create fire. As it moves in the steps of its beautiful dance, it bathes opponents in flames.

name: Cutiefly
pokedex_description: Because Cutiefly are able to sense auras, they can identify which flowers are about to bloom.

name: Ribombee
pokedex_description: It rolls up pollen into puffs. It makes many different varieties, some used as food and others for battle.

name: Rockruff
pokedex_description: It's a good Pokémon for beginners because of its friendlinless, but its disposition grows rougher as it grows up.

name: Lycanroc
pokedex_description: Its quick moves confuse its enemies. Well equipped with claws and fangs, it also uses the rocks in its mane as weapons.

name: Wishiwashi
pokedex_description: When in trouble, their eyes shine. The shining light attracts its comrades who will help them out.

name: Mareanie
pokedex_description: The coral that grows on Corsola's head is as good as a five-star banquet to this Pokémon.

name: Toxapex
pokedex_description: It crawls along the ocean floor on its 12 legs. It leaves a trail of Corsola bits scattered in its wake.

name: Mudbray
pokedex_description: The mud stuck to Mudbray's hooves enhances its grip and its powerful running gait.

name: Mudsdale
pokedex_description: It spits a mud that provides resistance to both wind and rain, so the walls of old houses were often coated with it.

name: Dewpider
pokedex_description: It crawls onto the land in search of food. Its water bubble allows it to breathe and protects its soft head.

name: Araquanid
pokedex_description: It delivers headbutts with the water bubbleon its head. Small Pokémon get sucked in the bubble and drown.

name: Fomantis
pokedex_description: During the day, it sleeps and soaks up light. When night falls, it walks around looking for a safer place to sleep.

name: Lurantis
pokedex_description: It fires beams from its petals. These beams are powerful enough to cleave through thick metal plates.

name: Morelull
pokedex_description: It scatters spores that flicker and glow. Anyone seeing these lights falls into a deep slumber.

name: Shiinotic
pokedex_description: Forests where Shiinotic live are treacherous to enter at night. People are confused by their lights and get lost.

name: Salandit
pokedex_description: It burns its bodily fluids to create poisonous gas. It attack its enemies once they inhale it.

name: Salazzle
pokedex_description: Filled with pheromones, its poisonous gas can be diluted to use in the production of perfumes.

name: Stufful
pokedex_description: Despite its adorable appearance, when it gets angry, its arms and legs could knock a pro wrestler sprawling.

name: Bewear
pokedex_description: This immensely dangerous Pokémon possesses overwhelming strength. Its habitat is generally offlimits.

name: Bounsweet
pokedex_description: A delectable aroma pours from its body. They are often swallowed by birds lured by that wafting deliciousness.

name: Steenee
pokedex_description: The sepals on its head are quite hard, so even if pecked by bird Pokémon, this Pokémon is totally fine.

name: Tsareena
pokedex_description: Its long, striking legs aren't just for show but to be used to kick with skill.

name: Comfey
pokedex_description: It attaches flowers to its highly nutritious vine. This revitalizes the flower and give off an aromatic scent.

name: Oranguru
pokedex_description: Known for its intelligence, this Pokémon looks down on inexperienced Trainers, so it's best for veteran Trainers.

name: Passimian
pokedex_description: They form groups of about 20 individuals. Their mutual bond is remarkable - They will never let down a comrade.

name: Wimpod
pokedex_description: As it desperately dashes off, the flailing of its many legs leave a sparkling clean path in its wake.

name: Golisopod
pokedex_description: With a flashing slash of its giant sharp claws, it cleaves seawater - or even air - right into two.

name: Sandygast
pokedex_description: Born from a sand mound playfully built by a child, this Pokémon embodies the grudges of the departed.

name: Palossand
pokedex_description: Buried beneath the castle are masses of bones from those whose vitality it has drained.

name: Pyukumuku
pokedex_description: It can eject its internal organs, which it uses to engulf its prey or battle enemies.

name: Código Cero
pokedex_description: The heavy control mask it wears suppresses its capabilities. This Pokémon has some hidden special power.

name: Silvally
pokedex_description: Its trust in its partner is what awakens it. This Pokémon is capable of changing its type.

name: Minior
pokedex_description: Strong impacts can knock it out of its shell. This Pokémon was born from mutated nanoparticles.

name: Komala
pokedex_description: The log it holds was give to it by its parents. It is also known to cling to the arm of a friendly Trainer.

name: Turtonator
pokedex_description: The shell on its back is chemically unstable and explodes violently. The hole in its stomach is its weak point.

name: Togedemaru
pokedex_description: The long hairs on its back act as lightning rods. The bolts of lightning it attracts are stored as energy.

name: Mimikyu
pokedex_description: Its actual appearance is unknown. When a scholar saw what was under its rag, it was overwhelmed by terror and died.

name: Bruxish
pokedex_description: It stuns its prey with psychokinesis and then grinds them to mush with its strong teeth.

name: Drampa
pokedex_description: It has a compassionate personality, but when angered, it completely destroys its surroundings with its breath.

name: Dhelmise
pokedex_description: Swinging its massive anchor, it can KO Wailord in a single blow. What appears to be green seaweed is actually its body.

name: Jangmo-o
pokedex_description: It expresses its feelings by smacking its scales. Metallic sounds echo through the tall mountains where it lives.

name: Hakamo-o
pokedex_description: It leaps at its prey with a courageous shout. Its scaly punches can tear its opponents to shreds.

name: Kommo-o
pokedex_description: When it spots enemies, it threatens them by jingling its scales. Weak opponents will crack and flee in panic.

name: Tapu Koko
pokedex_description: This guardian deity of Melemele is brimming with curiosity. It summons thunderclouds and stores their lightning.

name: Tapu Lele
pokedex_description: This guardian deity of Akala is guilelessly cruel. The fragrant aroma of flowers is the source of its energy.

name: Tapu Bulu
pokedex_description: This guardian deity of Ula'ula is lazy. It commands plants to immobilize its foes and then hits them with its horns.

name: Tapu Fini
pokedex_description: This guardian deity of Poni controls water. They say it can create pure water that will wash away any uncleanness.

name: Cosmog
pokedex_description: Its body is gaseous and frail. It slowsly grows as it collects dust from the atmosphere.

name: Cosmoem
pokedex_description: Motionless as if dead, its body is faintly warm to the touch. In the distant past, it was called the cocoon of stars.

name: Solgaleo
pokedex_description: At activation of its third eye, it departs for another world where it is said to live.

name: Lunala
pokedex_description: When its third eye activates, away it flies to another world where it is said to live.

name: Nihilego
pokedex_description: Se desconoce si este Ultraente posee consciencia propia, pero en ocasiones se comporta como una chica joven.

name: Buzzwole
pokedex_description: Un Ultraente procedente de otro mundo. Se desconoce si exhibe su robusto cuerpo a modo de amenaza o para que lo admiren.

name: Pheromosa
pokedex_description: Este Ultraente se muestra reacio al contacto, probablemente porque percibe inmundicia en todo cuanto le rodea.

name: Xurkitree
pokedex_description: Uno de los llamados Ultraentes. Algunos ejemplares plantan sus extremidades en el suelo como si fueran árboles y permanecen inmóviles.

name: Celesteela
pokedex_description: Varios testigos afirman haber visto como este Ultraente carbonizaba un bosque entero con el gas expelido por sus extremidades.

name: Kartana
pokedex_description: El cuerpo de este Ultraente es fino como el papel y tan cortante como una espada recién afilada.

name: Guzzlord
pokedex_description: Se dice que este Ultraente ha sido avistado devorando montañas enteras y tragándose prominentes edificios.

name: Necrozma
pokedex_description: Light is the source of its energy. If it isn't devouring light, impurities build up in it and on it, and Necrozma darkens and stops moving.

name: Magearna
pokedex_description: This artificial Pokémon, more than 500 years old, can understand human speech but cannot speak itself.

name: Marshadow
pokedex_description: Able to conceal itself in shadows, it never appears before human, so its very existence was the stuff of myth.

name: Poipole
pokedex_description: En su mundo, este Ultraente se considera tan entrañable como para ser elegido compañero de viaje.

name: Naganadel
pokedex_description: Una de las temibles criaturas conocidas como Ultraentes. En su cuerpo almacena cientos de litros de veneno.

name: Stakataka
pokedex_description: Extraña criatura que podría ser un Ultraente. Parece un muro rocoso hasta que se mueve de repente y ataca.

name: Blacephalon
pokedex_description: Se desliza hacia la gente. Entonces, sin previo aviso, desencadena la explosión de su propia cabeza. Aparentemente es un tipo de Ultraente.

name: Zeraora
pokedex_description: Se acerca a sus enemigos a la velocidad del rayo, luego los descuartiza con sus afiladas garras.

name: Meltan
pokedex_description: La mayor parte del cuerpo de Meltan está compuesta de metal líquido, lo que le confiere una silueta maleable y fluida.

name: Melmetal
pokedex_description: En la antigüedad, este Pokémon se ganó la adoración de la gente gracias a su capacidad para crear metal.

name: Grookey
pokedex_description: Al marcar el ritmo con su baqueta especial, produce unas ondas sonoras capaces de devolver la vitalidad a la flora.

name: Thwackey
pokedex_description: Los Thwackey que marcan el ritmo más contundente con sus dos baquetas son los más respetados por sus congéneres.

name: Rillaboom
pokedex_description: El percusionista con la técnica más depurada se convierte en líder. Son de carácter tranquilo y dan mucha importancia a la armonía del grupo.

name: Scorbunny
pokedex_description: Se pone a correr para elevar su temperatura corporal y propagar la energía ígnea por todo el cuerpo. Desata así su verdadera fuerza.

name: Raboot
pokedex_description: Su suave pelaje lo protege del frío y le permite incrementar todavía más la temperatura de sus movimientos de tipo Fuego.

name: Cinderace
pokedex_description: Convierte piedras en balones de fuego dándoles toques y, luego, chuta con fuerza hacia el rival para chamuscarlo.

name: Sobble
pokedex_description: Cuando se espanta, libera unas lágrimas con un factor lacrimógeno equivalente a 100 cebollas para hacer llorar también al rival.

name: Drizzile
pokedex_description: Crea bolas de agua con el líquido que segrega por las palmas de las manos y las usa en combate de forma estratégica.

name: Inteleon
pokedex_description: Dispara chorros de agua por la punta de los dedos a 3 mach de velocidad. Con su membrana nictitante puede ver los puntos débiles del rival.

name: Skwovet
pokedex_description: Siempre están comiendo bayas, por lo que son más robustos de lo que aparentan. Frecuentan los huertos en busca de su preciado manjar.

name: Greedent
pokedex_description: Se obceca tanto en acumular bayas en la cola que no se da ni cuenta de cuando tiene demasiadas y se le acaban cayendo.

name: Rookidee
pokedex_description: De naturaleza valiente, planta cara a cualquier rival, por muy fuerte que sea. Los contraataques que recibe le sirven para fortalecerse.

name: Corvisquire
pokedex_description: Su inteligencia le permite servirse de objetos. Por ejemplo, recoge y lanza piedras con las patas, o utiliza cuerdas para atrapar a su oponente.

name: Corviknight
pokedex_description: No tiene rival en los cielos. El acero negro y lustroso de su cuerpo intimida a cualquier adversario.

name: Blipbug
pokedex_description: Siempre está recopilando información, por lo que es muy inteligente, aunque su fuerza deja bastante que desear.

name: Dottler
pokedex_description: Apenas se mueve, pero está vivo. Se cree que adquiere poderes psíquicos mientras permanece recluido en su caparazón sin comer ni beber.

name: Orbeetle
pokedex_description: Este Pokémon es conocido por su inteligencia. El gran tamaño de su cerebro es un indicio de la magnitud de sus poderes psíquicos.

name: Nickit
pokedex_description: Marca a su presa sin ser advertido. Sigue el olor y, cuando el Pokémon baja la guardia, aprovecha para robarle.

name: Thievul
pokedex_description: Un Pokémon ágil y de afiladas garras que se alimenta de huevos y comida robados. Los Boltund son su enemigo natural.

name: Gossifleur
pokedex_description: Si planta su única extremidad inferior en la tierra y se expone a abundante luz solar, sus pétalos cobran un color vivo.

name: Eldegoss
pokedex_description: Las semillas que tiene entre la pelusa son muy nutritivas. Arrastradas por el viento, devuelven la vitalidad a la flora y a otros Pokémon.

name: Wooloo
pokedex_description: Su lana rizada es tan acolchada que no se hace daño ni aunque se caiga por un precipicio.

name: Dubwool
pokedex_description: Su lana es muy flexible. Las alfombras tejidas con ella adoptan una textura similar a la de las camas elásticas.

name: Chewtle
pokedex_description: Muerde todo lo que se le ponga por delante. Al parecer, lo hace para aliviar el dolor que siente cuando le crecen los incisivos.

name: Drednaw
pokedex_description: Un Pokémon de temperamento feroz que amenaza a su presa con sus fuertes mandíbulas, capaces de destrozar una barra de hierro.

name: Yamper
pokedex_description: Son muy glotones, por lo que ayudan a la gente a cambio de comida. Echan chispas al correr.

name: Boltund
pokedex_description: La electricidad que genera y envía a sus patas le ayuda a desplazarse rápidamente. Puede correr sin descanso durante tres días y tres noches.

name: Rolycoly
pokedex_description: Fue descubierto hace aproximadamente 400 años en una mina. Casi la totalidad de su cuerpo presenta una composición igual a la del carbón.

name: Carkol
pokedex_description: Gira la patas a gran velocidad para correr a unos 30 km/h. Emite llamas a una temperatura de 1000ºC.

name: Coalossal
pokedex_description: Aunque es de carácter sereno, monta en cólera si ve a seres humanos dañando una mina y reduce todo a cenizas con sus llamas a 1500 ºC.

name: Applin
pokedex_description: Habita durante toda su vida en el interior de una manzana. Finge ser una fruta para protegerse de los Pokémon pájaro, sus enemigos naturales.

name: Flapple
pokedex_description: Ha evolucionado tras ingerir una manzana ácida. Las bolsas de las mejillas albergan un fluido cuya extrema acidez llega a provocar quemaduras.

name: Appletun
pokedex_description: Ha evolucionado tras ingerir una manzana dulce. De ahí que el olor que emana para atraer a sus presas, los Pokémon insecto, sea tan agradable.

name: Silicobra
pokedex_description: Almacena la arena que ingiere al perforar hoyos en la saca del cuello, cuya capacidad llega a alcanzar incluso los 8 kg.

name: Sandaconda
pokedex_description: Se retuerce para expulsar por los orificios nasales hasta 100 kg de arena. La ausencia de esta mina su ánimo.

name: Cramorant
pokedex_description: Traga Arrokuda enteros debido a su glotonería, tan notable que en ocasiones ingiere hasta otros Pokémon sin querer.

name: Arrokuda
pokedex_description: Se siente muy orgulloso de su afilada mandíbula. En cuanto detecta el más mínimo movimiento, va directo al objetivo para cargar contra él.

name: Barraskewda
pokedex_description: Su mandíbula es tan puntiaguda como una lanza y tan dura como el acero. Al parecer, su carne es sorprendentemente deliciosa.

name: Toxel
pokedex_description: Segrega toxinas por la piel y las almacena en una bolsa de veneno interna. Tocarlo da calambre.

name: Toxtricity
pokedex_description: Cuando rasga las protuberancias del pecho para generar energía eléctrica, emite un sonido similar al de una guitarra, que reverbera en el entorno.

name: Sizzlipede
pokedex_description: Genera calor consumiendo el gas inflamable que almacena en su cuerpo. Los círculos amarillos del abdomen están particularmente calientes.

name: Centiskorch
pokedex_description: Cuando genera calor, su temperatura corporal alcanza aproximadamente los 800°C. Usa el cuerpo a modo de látigo para lanzarse al ataque.

name: Clobbopus
pokedex_description: Emerge a tierra firme en busca de alimento. Su extrema curiosidad lo induce a golpear con los tentáculos todo lo que entra en su campo visual.

name: Grapploct
pokedex_description: Todo su cuerpo es una mole de puro músculo. Utiliza los tentáculos para ejecutar técnicas de estrangulamiento con una formidable potencia.

name: Sinistea
pokedex_description: La espiral de su cuerpo líquido es su punto débil. Si se remueve, su complexión se desestabiliza y siente vértigo.

name: Polteageist
pokedex_description: Se hospeda en teteras dignas de un anticuario. Las originales son escasísimas, pero existe un gran número de burdas falsificaciones.

name: Hatenna
pokedex_description: Percibe los sentimientos de los seres vivos con la protuberancia de la cabeza. Solo abre su corazón a quienes muestren un carácter sosegado.

name: Hattrem
pokedex_description: Silencia a cualquiera que muestre una emoción intensa sin importar de quién se trate y recurre para ello a métodos a cuál más violento.

name: Hatterene
pokedex_description: Recibe el apodo de Hechicera del Bosque. Quienes arman demasiado barullo se exponen a ser despedazados por las garras de su tentáculo.

name: Impidimp
pokedex_description: Con el fin de revitalizarse, inhala por la nariz la energía negativa que desprenden tanto personas como Pokémon cuando están descontentos.

name: Morgrem
pokedex_description: Su estrategia consiste en postrarse ante el rival y fingir una disculpa para ensartarlo con el mechón que tiene en la espalda, afilado como lanza.

name: Grimmsnarl
pokedex_description: Cuando enrolla sus cabellos por todo el cuerpo, aumenta su potencia muscular. Posee una fuerza capaz de someter a Machamp.

name: Obstagoon
pokedex_description: Evoluciona tras haber librado numerosas peleas. El grito de guerra que profiere mientras pone los brazos en cruz atemoriza a cualquier rival.

name: Perrserker
pokedex_description: Lo que aparenta ser un yelmo de hierro, es realmente su pelaje. Este Pokémon vive dedicado a la emoción del combate.

name: Cursola
pokedex_description: Su energía espiritual ha aumentado hasta hacerlo desprenderse de su base caliza. Protege el alma del núcleo con su cuerpo espectral.

name: Sirfetch'd
pokedex_description: Este Sirfetch'd abandonó la vía guerrera cuando empezó a aficionarse a la rica bollería de Kalos.

name: Mr. Rime
pokedex_description: Es un bailarín consumado de claqué. Agita su bastón de hielo mientras exhibe su destreza con gráciles pasos.

name: Runerigus
pokedex_description: They pretend to be elaborate coffins to teach lessons to grave robbers. Their bodies are covered in pure gold.

name: Milcery
pokedex_description: Su cremoso cuerpo surgió a partir de la unión de partículas odoríferas de dulces aromas presentes en el aire.

name: Alcremie
pokedex_description: La nata que le brota de las manos es más dulce y sustanciosa cuando está feliz.

name: Falinks
pokedex_description: Este Pokémon consta de cinco subalternos y un líder, cuyas órdenes obedecen sin rechistar.

name: Pincurchin
pokedex_description: Libera electricidad por la punta de las púas. Con sus afilados dientes raspa las algas pegadas a las rocas para ingerirlas.

name: Snom
pokedex_description: Teje un hilo gélido que le permite aferrarse a las ramas y simula ser un carámbano mientras duerme.

name: Frosmoth
pokedex_description: La temperatura de sus alas es de -180°C. Sobrevuela el campo esparciendo sus gélidas escamas, como si de nieve se tratase.

name: Stonjourner
pokedex_description: Una vez al año y en una fecha concreta, tienen la costumbre de aparecer de la nada para reunirse y formar un círculo.

name: Eiscue
pokedex_description: Se enfría constantemente la cara con hielo por su escasa resistencia al calor. Utiliza el pelo de la cabeza para pescar en el mar.

name: Indeedee
pokedex_description: Con sus cuernos percibe las emociones de los seres vivos que se hallen cerca. Los sentimientos positivos constituyen su fuente de energía.

name: Morpeko
pokedex_description: Siempre tiene apetito, sin importar lo mucho que coma. Lleva con sumo cuidado las semillas que ha tostado con su propia electricidad.

name: Cufant
pokedex_description: Su constitución fornida le permite transportar sin inmutarse cargas de 5 toneladas. Utiliza la trompa para excavar la tierra.

name: Copperajah
pokedex_description: Su piel verdosa es resistente al agua. Proviene de tierras lejanas y presta ayuda a las personas en la realización de ciertos trabajos.

name: Dracozolt
pokedex_description: La robustez de su tren inferior lo hacía invencible en la antigüedad, pero se extinguió tras comerse todas las plantas de las que se nutría.

name: Arctozolt
pokedex_description: Antiguamente vivía en el mar y usaba el hielo del cuerpo para conservar los alimentos. Su extrema lentitud, sin embargo, lo condenó a la extinción.

name: Dracovish
pokedex_description: Su excelente capacidad motriz y la fuerza de su mandíbula lo hacían antaño invencible, pero dar caza a todas sus presas propició su extinción.

name: Arctovish
pokedex_description: Aunque la piel de su rostro era capaz de resistir cualquier ataque, su dificultad para respirar acabó provocando su extinción.

name: Duraludon
pokedex_description: Su cuerpo, similar a un metal pulido, es tan ligero como robusto. Sin embargo, tiene el defecto de que se oxida con facilidad.

name: Dreepy
pokedex_description: Habitaba los mares en tiempos inmemoriales. Ha revivido en forma de Pokémon de tipo Fantasma para vagar por su antigua morada.

name: Drakloak
pokedex_description: Vuela a una velocidad de 200 km/h. Lucha junto a un Dreepy, al que cuida hasta el momento de su evolución.

name: Dragapult
pokedex_description: Al parecer, los Dreepy que residen en sus cuernos esperan con ilusión el momento de ser propulsados a velocidad supersónica.

name: Zacian
pokedex_description: Este Pokémon está considerado como un héroe de leyenda. Absorbe el metal para transformarlo y emplearlo como armamento.

name: Zamazenta
pokedex_description: Este Pokémon se erigió en salvador de Galar, tras unir fuerzas con un rey de los hombres. Absorbe el metal para utilizarlo en combate.

name: Eternatus
pokedex_description: Se alimenta de la energía que brota de la tierra de Galar absorbiéndola por el núcleo del pecho.

name: Kubfu
pokedex_description: Al tirar de los mechones blancos de la cabeza, acrecienta su espíritu luchador y empieza a acumular fuerza en el órgano de su bajo vientre.

name: Urshifu
pokedex_description: Vive en en zonas montañosas en áreas recónditas, donde entrena corriendo por escarpados riscos para fortalecer sus piernas y refinar su técnica.

name: Zarude
pokedex_description: Las lianas que le brotan del cuerpo nutren y fertilizan el mantillo del bosque cuando se le desprenden.

name: Regieleki
pokedex_description: Su cuerpo entero es energía eléctrica. Por lo visto, quitarle los anillos que lleva libera su poder oculto.

name: Regidrago
pokedex_description: Todo su cuerpo es una gema de energía dragón cristalizada. Se cree que posee los poderes de todos los Pokémon dragón.

name: Glastrier
pokedex_description: Cuenta con una fuerza física sobrecogedora. La máscara de hielo que le cubre el rostro es cien veces más dura que el diamante.

name: Spectrier
pokedex_description: Examina su entorno con todos los sentidos, salvo la vista. Se dice que sus coces son capaces de robarle el alma a quien las recibe.

name: Calyrex
pokedex_description: Un Pokémon muy compasivo agraciado con el poder de la curación. Reinó en Galar en tiempos remotos.

name: Cefireon
pokedex_description: Se ha hecho uno con el viento y ahora es capaz de dominarlo a voluntad. Vuela a gran velocidad atravesando nubes y tormentas.

name: Maidible
pokedex_description: Its giant jaws are actually steel horns that transformed. It fools foes into complacency with its adorable gestures, then chomps them with its huge jaws.

name: Zippectre
pokedex_description: An abandoned plush doll became this Pokémon. They are said to live in garbage dumps and wander about in search of the children that threw them away.

name: Soundow
pokedex_description: Its auditory sense is astounding. It has a radar-like ability to understand its surrounding through slight sounds.

name: Kleavor
pokedex_description: A Scizor has a body with the hardness of steel. It is not easily fazed by ordinary sorts of attacks. It flaps its wings to regulate its body temperature.

name: Wyrdeer
pokedex_description: Stantler's magnificent antlers were once traded at high prices as works of art. As a result, this Pokémon was hunted close to extinction.

name: Basculegion
pokedex_description: Red and blue Basculin usually do not get along, but sometimes members of one school mingle with the other's schooL.

name: Overqwil
pokedex_description: A Qwilfish uses the pressure of water it swallows to shoot toxic quills all at once from all over its body. It finds swimming to be somewhat challenging.

name: Sneasler
pokedex_description: They live in cold regions, forming groups of four or five that hunt prey with impressive coordination.

name: Missingno
pokedex_description: La Pokedex no tiene información sobre este Pokemon.

name: Sprigatito
pokedex_description: Su sedoso pelaje se asemeja en composición a las plantas. Se lava la cara con diligencia para que no se le seque.

name: Floragato
pokedex_description: Maneja diestramente la vid oculta bajo su largo pelaje y propina latigazos al enemigo con el capullo endurecido de la punta.

name: Meowscarada
pokedex_description: Se sirve de la luz que reflejan los tricomas de su manto de hojas para camuflar la vid y crear la ilusión óptica de que la flor flota en el aire.

name: Fuecoco
pokedex_description: Yace sobre rocas calientes, cuyo calor transforma en energía ígnea tras absorberlo por sus escamas rectangulares.

name: Crocalor
pokedex_description: La mezcla de energía ígnea con el exceso de su propia fuerza vital ha tomado la forma de una bola de fuego de aspecto oval sobre su cabeza.

name: Skeledirge
pokedex_description: Se dice que el pájaro flamígero al que da forma su canto es un espíritu que moraba en la bola de fuego que le coronaba la cabeza.

name: Quaxly
pokedex_description: Un Pokémon llegado hace tiempo desde tierras lejanas y ya establecido en la región. El gel que secreta por las plumas repele el agua y la mugre.

name: Quaxwell
pokedex_description: Fortalece las extremidades corriendo con tesón por los bajíos. Compite con los suyos para ver cuál posee una técnica más grácil con las patas.

name: Quaquaval
pokedex_description: Realiza una exótica danza mientras controla la tremenda fuerza de sus extremidades, capaces de hacer volcar un camión de una patada.

name: Lechonk
pokedex_description: Posee un olfato muy desarrollado que emplea únicamente para buscar comida, actividad a la que dedica el día entero.

name: Oinkologne
pokedex_description: Su piel suave y lustrosa es su mayor orgullo. Desprende una fragancia concentrada por la punta de la cola.

name: Dudunsparce
pokedex_description: Usa su dura cola para horadar el lecho rocoso en las profundidades de la tierra y establecer su madriguera, cuyos túneles se extienden 10 km.

name: Tarountula
pokedex_description: La bola de hilo que le rodea el cuerpo es lo bastante elástica como para repeler las guadañas de los Scyther, su enemigo natural.

name: Spidops
pokedex_description: Se adhiere con su hilo a ramas y techos, por los que se desplaza en silencio. Acaba con su presa antes de que esta se percate de su presencia.

name: Nymble
pokedex_description: Mantiene plegado su tercer par de patas, cuya fuerza le permite saltar a más de 10 m de altura para huir en caso de apuro.

name: Lokix
pokedex_description: Cuando decide luchar sin cuartel, se alza con su tercer par de patas y entra en modo asalto. Acaba con el rival en un abrir y cerrar de ojos.

name: Rellor
pokedex_description: Mezcla tierra, arena y energía psíquica para crear una bola de barro que atesora por encima de su propia vida.

name: Rabsca
pokedex_description: El cuerpo que sostiene la bola apenas se mueve, por lo que se cree que el cuerpo en el interior de esta es quien controla sus acciones.

name: Greavard
pokedex_description: Se cree que es la reencarnación de un Pokémon perro vagabundo que murió sin haber tenido contacto con humanos.

name: Houndstone
pokedex_description: Pasa la mayor parte del tiempo durmiendo en cementerios. De todos los Pokémon perro, es el que profesa una mayor lealtad por su Entrenador.

name: Flittle
pokedex_description: La punta de sus extremidades levita a 1 cm del suelo a causa del poder psíquico que emiten los volantes de su abdomen.

name: Espathra
pokedex_description: Baña al rival con el poder psíquico que emana de sus grandes ojos y lo inmoviliza. A pesar de su aspecto, posee un temperamento feroz.

name: Farigiraf
pokedex_description: Las ondas cerebrales de la cola y la cabeza van al compás, lo que le confiere poderes psíquicos diez veces más potentes que los de los Girafarig.

name: Dondozo
pokedex_description: Le gusta mucho comer, pero no se le da bien cazar, por lo que aúna fuerzas con Tatsugiri con el fin de capturar presas.

name: Veluza
pokedex_description: Al desechar la carne que no necesita, agudiza la mente y sus poderes psíquicos se incrementan. Dicha carne tiene un sabor suave pero exquisito.

name: Finizen
pokedex_description: Le gusta jugar con sus congéneres con el anillo de agua de su aleta caudal. Utiliza ultrasonidos para percibir las emociones de otros seres.

name: Palafin
pokedex_description: Cambia de forma en cuanto recibe una señal de socorro de sus compañeros. Nunca se transforma delante de nadie.

name: Smoliv
pokedex_description: Se defiende de sus rivales segregando por el fruto de su cabeza un aceite tan amargo y agrio que cualquiera daría un respingo al probarlo.

name: Dolliv
pokedex_description: No duda en compartir su delicioso aceite de fresco aroma. Convive con los seres humanos desde hace mucho tiempo.

name: Arboliva
pokedex_description: Es pacífico y compasivo. Comparte su delicioso y nutritivo aceite con los Pokémon que han perdido las fuerzas.

name: Capsakid
pokedex_description: Cuanto más se expone al sol, más aumenta la cantidad de capsaicinoides de su cuerpo y, por lo tanto, la pungencia de sus movimientos.

name: Scovillain
pokedex_description: La cabeza roja transforma los capsaicinoides de su cuerpo en energía flamígera, lo que le permite arrojar llamaradas extremadamente abrasadoras.

name: Tadbulb
pokedex_description: Produce electricidad agitando la cola. Si siente peligro, hace parpadear su cabeza para alertar a sus compañeros.

name: Bellibolt
pokedex_description: Puede generar grandes cantidades de energía expandiendo y contrayendo su elástico cuerpo gracias a la dinamo de su ombligo.

name: Varoom
pokedex_description: Se dice que surgió cuando un misterioso Pokémon venenoso tomó posesión de un motor abandonado en un desguace.

name: Revavroom
pokedex_description: Posee ocho cilindros, con los que genera energía haciendo estallar el gas que produce al mezclar los minerales de las rocas con su veneno.

name: Orthworm
pokedex_description: Cuando lo atacan, usa los pelos de su cuerpo a modo de puños y hace llover un aluvión de puñetazos sobre sus enemigos.

name: Tandemaus
pokedex_description: Cuando encuentran un material que les parece útil para su nido, lo recortan con sus incisivos y lo acarrean, todo en perfecta compenetración.

name: Maushold
pokedex_description: Construyen grandes nidos que dividen en varias cámaras destinadas a distintas funciones, como dormir o comer.

name: Cetoddle
pokedex_description: Los miembros de esta especie, emparentada al parecer con los Wailmer, abandonaron hace ya mucho tiempo el mar para vivir en tierra firme.

name: Cetitan
pokedex_description: Este Pokémon vive en áreas cubiertas de nieve y hielo. Se protege con su fuerte musculatura y una gruesa capa de grasa subcutánea.

name: Frigibax
pokedex_description: Absorbe el calor a través de la placa dorsal y lo convierte en energía gélida. Cuanto más alta es la temperatura, más energía acumula.

name: Arctibax
pokedex_description: Congela el aire a su alrededor para cubrirse el rostro con una máscara de hielo protectora y dotar su placa dorsal de cuchillas glaciales.

name: Baxcalibur
pokedex_description: Exhala un aliento extremadamente frío por la boca que es capaz de congelar al instante incluso magma al rojo vivo.

name: Tatsugiri
pokedex_description: Pokémon dragón de pequeño tamaño. Vive en la boca de un Dondozo para protegerse de los ataques de los depredadores.

name: Cyclizar
pokedex_description: Según parece, ha permitido que los humanos monten en él desde tiempos remotos. Aparece en pinturas rupestres de hace diez mil años.

name: Pawmi
pokedex_description: Como las bolsas de sus mejillas están poco desarrolladas, genera electricidad frotándolas con las almohadillas de sus patas delanteras.

name: Pawmo
pokedex_description: Cuando su manada se ve amenazada, atacan a la vanguardia usando un arte marcial caracterizado por el empleo de descargas eléctricas.

name: Pawmot
pokedex_description: Este Pokémon es normalmente bastante calmado, pero, una vez en combate, derriba a sus rivales con movimientos de una velocidad vertiginosa.

name: Wattrel
pokedex_description: Los huesos de sus alas producen electricidad con las corrientes de aire. Para cazar, se zambulle en el mar y electrocuta a su presa.

name: Kilowattrel
pokedex_description: Aumenta la intensidad de su electricidad al inflar su saco gular. Es capaz de recorrer 700 km en un día impulsado por las corrientes de aire.

name: Bombirdier
pokedex_description: Mete cosas en su bolsa, fabricada con el plumón de su pecho y con plumas mudadas, para luego dejarlas caer desde las alturas por diversión.

name: Squawkabilly
pokedex_description: Prefieren vivir en las ciudades. Forman bandadas según el color de su plumaje y libran disputas por el control de los territorios.

name: Flamigo
pokedex_description: Al parecer, se anudan la base del cuello para impedir que la energía que tienen almacenada en el estómago escape por el pico.

name: Klawf
pokedex_description: Acecha a sus presas colgado cabeza abajo de los acantilados, pero no puede aguantar así mucho tiempo porque se le sube la sangre a la cabeza.

name: Nacli
pokedex_description: Surgen de estratos salinos subterráneos. Antaño se los tenía en alta estima, pues compartían su sal, un mineral por entonces muy preciado.

name: Naclstack
pokedex_description: Escupe sal para recubrir con ella a sus presas y someterlas a un proceso de salazón que extrae la humedad de sus cuerpos.

name: Garganacl
pokedex_description: Cuando encuentra a un Pokémon herido, frota las puntas de los dedos para rociarlo con sal y curar rápidamente incluso las heridas más graves.

name: Glimmet
pokedex_description: Absorbe nutrientes de las paredes de las cuevas. Cubre su cuerpo con pétalos hechos de energía venenosa cristalizada.

name: Glimmora
pokedex_description: En cuanto percibe peligro, abre sus pétalos de cristal y despide rayos por su cuerpo en forma de cono.

name: Shroodle
pokedex_description: Es manso, pero muerde y paraliza a quien lo enfada con sus afilados incisivos impregnados de toxinas.

name: Grafaiai
pokedex_description: El color de su saliva venenosa varía según su alimentación. Se embadurna los dedos con ella para pintar motivos en los árboles del bosque.

name: Fidough
pokedex_description: Resulta húmedo y suave al tacto. Hace fermentar las cosas a su alrededor con la levadura de su aliento.

name: Dachsbun
pokedex_description: El fragante aroma que despide su cuerpo favorece el crecimiento del trigo, por lo que lo aprecian mucho en las comunidades agrícolas.

name: Maschiff
pokedex_description: Mantiene el ceño fruncido para que sus rivales lo tomen en serio, pero hasta el niño más llorón estallaría en carcajadas al ver su mueca.

name: Mabosstiff
pokedex_description: Almacena energía en la papada y la libera toda de golpe para arrasar con sus rivales.

name: Bramblin
pokedex_description: Se dice que este Pokémon nace cuando las almas en pena terminan enredadas en la hierba seca tras ser arrastradas por el viento.

name: Brambleghast
pokedex_description: Despliega las ramas para engullir a sus presas. Cuando ha terminado de absorber su energía vital, las escupe.

name: Gimmighoul
pokedex_description: El cofre en el que nació data de hace 1500 años aproximadamente. Absorbe la energía vital de los granujas que intentan hacerse con su tesoro.

name: Gholdengo
pokedex_description: Se dice que su cuerpo está formado por 1000 monedas. Es capaz de hacer buenas migas con cualquiera rápidamente por su sociabilidad.

name: Tinkatink
pokedex_description: Agita su martillo forjado a mano para ahuyentar a posibles amenazas, pero los Pokémon que se alimentan a base de metal suelen robárselo.

name: Tinkatuff
pokedex_description: Asalta el séquito entero de un Bisharp para reunir metal con el que forjar su enorme y robusto martillo.

name: Tinkaton
